[center][size=18pt][b][i]Step 1.[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center]Declaring INT's.[/center]

Ok , first we will declare these [i][u]INT's[/u][/i]

[code=cmf]public int startersfail = 0;
public long beginners = 0;[/code]

So that our compiler wont throw an errors back to our faces telling us that he couldn't find the correct symbol ;).

[center][size=18pt][b][i]Step 2.[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center]Providing the character to have [u][i]startersfail / beginners[/i][/u] options.[/center]

Look for 

